 first colony in North America in 1585 as a way to generate additional wealth. The colony was named Virginia, after the virgin Queen Elizabeth I.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705208,"age":67,"year":"1587","julianDay":2300700,"title":"Elizabeth I Signs Death Warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots","description":"Elizabeth I signed the death warrant for Mary, Queen of Scots, on February 1, 1587, as she was found guilty of plotting to assasinate Elizabeth. Mary, Queen of Scots, was beheaded at Fotheringhay Castle in England on February 8, 1587.","url":"https://www.elizabethi.org/mary_queen_of_scots/","urlTitle":"Elizabeth I.org - Mary Queen of Scots","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705212,"age":100,"year":"1620","julianDay":2312753,"title":"The Pilgrims Board the Mayflower","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"John Cowbaine was born in 1520, in Kirkham, Lancashire, England as the son of Mr Coubaine or Cowbrone. He married Elizabeth Thornton about 1540, in St Michael, Sussex, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1520–":"1520–Surnud","1520–Male":"1520–Surnud","1520–1572":"1520–1572","1542–1586":"1542–1586","1550–Male":"1550–Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1501–1520":"1501–1520","1550":"1550","1572":"1572","1569":"1569","1558":"1558","1501":"1501","1620":"1620","1587":"1587","1520":"1520","ABT 1540":"umbes 1540","1542":"1542","1586":"1586","1585":"1585","13 JAN 1547":"13. jaanuar 1547","1549":"1549","StMichael Ki